                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13961876" author="sslavic" created="Mon, 7 Apr 2014 14:26:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Assigned issue to packaging component&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13961880" author="sslavic" created="Mon, 7 Apr 2014 14:30:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This bug is caused by new and incomplete migration to gradle build, introduced in 0.8.1 through &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-1171&quot; title=&quot;Gradle build for Kafka&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-1171&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-1171&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
Before this 0.8.0 had sources and javadoc jars published (see &lt;a href=&quot;http://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/apache/kafka/kafka_2.10/0.8.0/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13969738" author="jjkoshy" created="Tue, 15 Apr 2014 16:59:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Will upload a patch today.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13969975" author="jjkoshy" created="Tue, 15 Apr 2014 19:39:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Created reviewboard &lt;a href=&quot;https://reviews.apache.org/r/20376/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://reviews.apache.org/r/20376/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 against branch origin/0.8.1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13969978" author="jjkoshy" created="Tue, 15 Apr 2014 19:40:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The above patch should apply to trunk as well, but I will rebase if necessary. The docsJar_2_8_2 task fails for some reason, but all the other tasks pass.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13970367" author="joestein" created="Wed, 16 Apr 2014 02:42:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;./gradlew srcJar worked great &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;however the docsJar_2_8_2  error is stopping ./gradlew releaseTarGzAll from working &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/sad.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; trying to get a stacktrace out of it&lt;/p&gt;


</comment>
                            <comment id="13970390" author="joestein" created="Wed, 16 Apr 2014 03:40:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;i ran with stacktrace, debug and info &lt;a href=&quot;https://gist.github.com/joestein/10803377#file-kafka-1362-L296&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://gist.github.com/joestein/10803377#file-kafka-1362-L296&lt;/a&gt; googled around a bit looks like a bug in 2.8.1 scaladoc itself &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.scala-lang.org/browse/SI-4284&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://issues.scala-lang.org/browse/SI-4284&lt;/a&gt; but fixed in 2.9.0 not sure yet if there is a workaround or what exactly in the code is causing this that we can change to subvert it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13970541" author="sslavic" created="Wed, 16 Apr 2014 07:34:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Consider dropping Scala 2.8.x support. I&apos;ve just created a separate request for that (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-1399&quot; title=&quot;Drop Scala 2.8.x support&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-1399&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-1399&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13971668" author="jjkoshy" created="Wed, 16 Apr 2014 17:13:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=joestein&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;joestein&quot;&gt;joestein&lt;/a&gt; I think I ran across a similar bug report earlier, but couldn&apos;t explain why that would affect the 2.8.2 scaladoc build.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13971669" author="jjkoshy" created="Wed, 16 Apr 2014 17:14:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We could just get rid of 2_8_2. We would still have 2_8_0&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13973474" author="joestein" created="Thu, 17 Apr 2014 22:03:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;2.8.0 is so much older and worse (arguably) and not used if we drop support for 2.8.2 we might as well do it for 2.8.0, we should have some consensus to-do that though IMHO it falls under &quot;release plan&quot; and would require a Lazy majority to pass.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13973529" author="jjkoshy" created="Thu, 17 Apr 2014 22:48:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We could, but it&apos;s just that there are a couple of users on 2.8 still - including LinkedIn. Since only the docs jar task is failing, I thought it would be sufficient to just remove 2.8.2 from docsJarAll.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13973535" author="joestein" created="Thu, 17 Apr 2014 22:58:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;ok&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13974454" author="jjkoshy" created="Fri, 18 Apr 2014 20:40:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to both 0.8.1 and trunk&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Filed &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-1406&quot; title=&quot;Fix scaladoc/javadoc warnings&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-1406&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-1406&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to address the warnings when generating javadocs/scaladocs.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14020794" author="dwegener" created="Sat, 7 Jun 2014 12:45:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;kafka_2.10-0.8.1.1-sources.jar in maven central ist empty (see &lt;a href=&quot;http://search.maven.org/#artifactdetails%7Corg.apache.kafka%7Ckafka_2.10%7C0.8.1.1%7Cjar&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://search.maven.org/#artifactdetails%7Corg.apache.kafka%7Ckafka_2.10%7C0.8.1.1%7Cjar&lt;/a&gt;). Is this intentional?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14105599" author="ianfriedman" created="Thu, 21 Aug 2014 17:03:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Echoing the comment about the sources jar being empty. Can we get a resolution on this please? &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jjkoshy&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jjkoshy&quot;&gt;jjkoshy&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14109362" author="bcalmac" created="Mon, 25 Aug 2014 17:35:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue should be reopened. The sources jar for 0.8.1.1 on Maven Central is empty.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14133550" author="junrao" created="Mon, 15 Sep 2014 03:48:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The maven issue should be fixed in kafka-1502.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
